Sixty nine patients were admitted in the Intensive Care Unit on Sunday due to Covid-19 complications. From the number, 23 were on ventilatory support while 36 were on supplemental oxygen, Health CS Mutahi Kagwe confirmed in a statement. Ten more patients were under observation. “Another 16 patients are separately on supplementary oxygen with all of whom are in the general wards. No patient is in the high dependency unit,” Kagwe said. The CS confirmed that 465 more people had tested positive for the virus from a sample size of 5,691 tests conducted in 24 hours. This represents a positivity rate of 8.1 per cent. The new cases comprised of 422 Kenyans and 43 foreign nationals aged between one year and 91 years old. “Unfortunately, two patients have succumbed to the disease pushing our cumulative fatalities to 1,876. Our sincere condolences to the families and friends who have lost their loved ones,” the CS said. Data from the ministry showed that here were 488 patients admitted in various health facilities countrywide, while 1,394 were on home based isolation and care. “Today, 20 patients have recovered from the disease, 17 from the various health facilities countrywide while three are from the home based isolation and care. The total recoveries now stand at 87,570.” In terms of distribution of cases per county, Nairobi recorded 310 new cases followed by Kiambu with 54, Mombasa and Tharaka Nithi with 11 cases each, Kajiado with 10, Machakos with nine, Busia with eight and Kitui with seven cases. Other counties that recorded new infections include Meru, Laikipia, Kilifi and Uasin Gishu with three cases each while Kwale, Makueni, Marsabit,murang’a anf Isiolo recorded one case each.